condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.4 | Description :MOH sthall establish and maintain an oversight committee for the project | DueDate :18-Jul-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.5 | Description :The Recipient shall appoint 30 days after effectiveness date an internationallyqualified financial management specialist, with terms of reference and experience satisfactory to the Association | Due Date:18-Jul-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.5 | Description :The Recipient shall appoint 30 days after effectiveness date an internationallyqualified procurement specialist, with terms of reference and experience satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :18-Jul-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.A.1 | Description :The Recipient shall: (a) carry out the Project in accordance with the ProjectOperations Manual that is revised to reflect the restructured Project; and (b) not amend, abrogate, suspend, or waive any provisionof said Project Operations Manual without the prior concurrence of the Project Steering Committee (PSC) and the Association. | DueDate :04-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.A.2.(a) | Description :The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain, within MoH, a ProjectSteering Committee with representation from Establish and maintain a Project Steering Committee to provide oversight for theProject implementation and will convene on a regular basis. | Due Date :04-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.A.2.(b) | Description :The Recipient shall maintain, throughout the period of implementation aProject Management Team in a department in MoH in charge ofpartnership management responsible for coordination, M&E ofimplementation, and will have adequate and qualified resources to carryout its functions per Operations Manual. | Due Date:04-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.A.2.(c) | Description :The Recipient shall maintain or appoint, and thereafter maintain until thecompletion of the Project: (i) a qualified financial management and budget specialist, (ii) a qualified procurement specialist,(iii) a qualified Project accountant, and (iv) a partnershipmanagement Specialist; all will have TOR and a demonstrated competencesatisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :15-Dec-2015

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.A.3 | Description :The Recipient shall no later than 30th November of each year, prepare a draftannual activity plan and combined sources of budgets for the health sector in line with its planning and budgeting procedures andcalendar, to include proposed allocations for gov't budget and donor resources; and seek approval by Project Steering Committee andthe Association. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.A.3(a) | Description :The Recipient shall, no later than 30th November of each year, prepare anannual work plan and combined sources budgets (AWPB) for the health sector in line with its planning and budgeting procedures andcalendar | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.B.1/2 | Description :The Recipient shall make Grants available for Districts to carry out DistrictSubprojects under Component 1(c) of the Project in accordance with eligibility criteria and procedures acceptable to theAssociation, as further detailed in the Project Operations Manual. | Due Date :31-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.D.1 | Description :The Recipient shall, through MoH: (a) implement, and cause to implement, theGuidelines on Maintenance, Handling and Disposal of Asbestos Materials and Asbestos Waste for all civil work activities; and (b)maintain, and cause to be maintained, policies and procedures adequate to enable it to monitor and evaluate, in accordance withguidelines acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :31-Dec-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.D.2 | Description :The Recipient shall, through MoH: (a) ensure that each referral hospital andhealth district have at least one (1) functioning gasifier for managing health care wastes by December 31, 2008; and (b) ensurethat the health facilities without a gasifier bring their hazardous wastes to the nearest community health center for treatmentprior to disposal. | Due Date :31-Dec-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.II.A.1 | Description :The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project andprepare Project Reports. Each Project Report shall cover the period of one (1) calendar quarter, and shall be furnished to theProject Steering Committee and the Association not later than forty five (45) days after the end of the period covered by suchreport. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.II.A.1(a) | Description :The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project andprepare Project Reports. Each Project Report shall cover the period of one (1) calendar semester, and shall be furnished to theAssociation not later than one (1) month after the end of the period covered by such report. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.II.B.1/2 | Description :The Recipient shall maintain an FMS in accordance with provisions of Section5.09 of the General Conditions, and prepare and furnish to the Association, not later than forty five (45) days after the end ofeach calendar quarter, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project covering the quarter, in form and substance satisfactoryto the Association. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.II.B.2 | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to the Association, not later than one(1) month after the end of each calendar quarter, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project covering the quarter, in formand substance satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.II.B.3 | Description :The Recipient shall have its Financial Statements audited in accordance withthe provisions of Section 4.09(b) of the General Conditions. Each audit of the Financial Statements shall cover the period of one(1) fiscal year of the Recipient and shall be furnished to the Association not later than six (6) months after the end of suchperiod. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.II.B.3/4 | Description :The Recipient shall have its Project Financial Statements (PFS) audited.Each audit of the PFS shall cover the period of one (1) fiscal year of the Recipient. The audited PFS for each such period shallbe furnished to the Association not later than six (6) months after the end of such period (or not later than nine (9) months ifusing MoH's imprest system for District Subprojects). | Frequency :Yearly
